defining var(s) in css

scrolling behavior in css

never underestimate the power of the dev console
    can edit all flexbox properties in the inspect tool

flex direction: column = main y axis
    row: x = main axis

justify = y axis
    align = x axis

netflix scrolling

media queries: can be used to change styles based on viewport, 
    using min-width: checks for a minimum, using max-width = maximum value
    can use "or" and "and" to mix and match rules
    check for these breakpoints by 
        adjusting the dimensions in the inspect tool in your browser
    for example you can increase font size based on screen size
    media queries belong at the bottom of your css direction

